The paper deals with privacy concerns in distributed computations, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). It also involves analyzing data in a distributed manner, which can be categorized under distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the accuracy requirements for computing different functions, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with private data analysis, which can be categorized under databases (cs.DB).
